<seg id="1">Tearing vegetables in shops heats up feelings: This is how much you can actually save by removing "extra parts"</seg>
<seg id="2">Can cauliflower leaves be removed before weighing?</seg>
<seg id="3">What about the large top of a pineapple? After all, it weighs who knows how much.</seg>
<seg id="4">People are divided: for some, this is an indication of extreme stinginess, some do not want to pay for the parts that they will not use and that they would throw away anyway.</seg>
